<span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span> RMB’s experience and insight as a financier across various infrastructure sub-sectors – spanning energy, ports, logistics and healthcare – allow it to help bridge the infrastructure deficit and provide funding solutions in the form of advice and balance sheet support. The bank’s infrastructure finance team’s multidisciplinary approach enables it to originate, structure and execute transactions that speak to local market conditions, while matching local market liquidity constraints with the appetite of international investor pools. Mphokolo Makara, infrastructure finance transactor at RMB, chats to Moneyweb editor Ryk van Niekerk about the trends and opportunities in this area of business. For more information, click here. Brought to you by Rand Merchant Bank (RMB).